Task 4: Recurrence Validation

calls1=0
def T1(n):
    global calls1
    calls1+=1
    if n<=1:
        return 1
    return T1(n//2)+n

calls2=0
def T2(n):
    global calls2
    calls2+=1
    if n<=1:
        return 1
    return T2(n//2)+T2(n//2)+n

for n in [16,32]:
    calls1=0
    T1(n)
    print("T(n)=T(n/2)+n calls:",calls1)

    calls2=0
    T2(n)
    print("T(n)=2T(n/2)+n calls:",calls2)


T(n)=T(n/2)+n calls: 5
T(n)=2T(n/2)+n calls: 31
T(n)=T(n/2)+n calls: 6
T(n)=2T(n/2)+n calls: 63

T(n)=T(n/2)+n gives linear complexity O(n). T(n)=2T(n/2)+n gives O(n log n). Recursive calls confirm growth trend.


